This paper deals with the problem of generating textual paraphrases, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes new evaluation metrics and learning criteria for this task, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of NLP that deals with text generation and transfer. Specifically, the paper focuses on the setting without parallel data, which is a challenging problem in NLP and requires unsupervised learning techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of NLP that deal with unsupervised learning (cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) as well as computer vision (cs.CV), since text generation is often used in conjunction with image processing.
